  "arbitrary": [
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Function of unitary fourier transform (uft) and utilities"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "This module implements the unitary fourier transform, also known as the ortho-normal transform. It is especially useful for convolution [1], as it respects the Parseval equality. The value of the null frequency is equal to"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "type": "math",
          "value": "\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{n}} \\sum_i x_i"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "so the Fourier transform has the same energy as the original image (see "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "image_quad_norm"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " function). The transform is applied from the last axis for performance (assuming a C-order array input)."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "level": 0,
      "target": null,
      "title": null,
      "type": "Section"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "placeholder": "footnote",
          "type": "Unimplemented",
          "value": ".. [1] B. R. Hunt \"A matrix theory proof of the discrete convolution\n       theorem\", IEEE Trans. on Audio and Electroacoustics,\n       vol. au-19, no. 4, pp. 285-288, dec. 1971"
        }
      ],
